Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} before baking.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}, onion and @diced chorizo{90%g} to the pan and stir-fry until the onion has softened and the chicken has started to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} onto a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of @oil{}. Stir through half the garlic. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Set aside for now.

Meanwhile, add the @risotto rice{175%g} and remaining garlic to the ovenproof pan, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour the @boiled water for the risotto{600%ml} and @chicken stock paste{15%g} into the risotto rice. Stir to combine.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with foil).

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Pop the tomato parcel onto a small #baking tray{}.

Roast on the bottom shelf of your oven until softened, ~{15-20%minutes}.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and stir through the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @butter{20%g} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the oven-baked risotto between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the roasted tomatoes along with their juices. Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} leaves.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!